description: Commands to manage private endpoint connections.

commands.name: az grafana private-endpoint-connection delete
commands.syntax:
az grafana private-endpoint-connection delete [--ids]
                                              [--name]
                                              [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                              [--resource-group]
                                              [--subscription]
                                              [--workspace-name]
                                              [--yes]

commands.name: az grafana private-endpoint-connection show
commands.summary: Get a specific private endpoint connection.

commands.name: az grafana private-endpoint-connection update
commands.syntax:
az grafana private-endpoint-connection update [--add]
                                              [--connection-state]
                                              [--force-string {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                              [--group-ids]
                                              [--ids]
                                              [--name]
                                              [--no-wait {0, 1, f, false, n, no, t, true, y, yes}]
                                              [--remove]
                                              [--resource-group]
                                              [--set]
                                              [--subscription]
                                              [--workspace-name]
examples: az grafana private-endpoint-connection update -n MyPrivateEndpoint -g MyResourceGroup --workspace-name MyGrafana --private-link-service-connection-state description="My response message" status="Approved"

commands.name: az grafana private-endpoint-connection wait
commands.summary: Place the CLI in a waiting state until a condition is met.
